.gov/data-products/state-fact-sheets/state-data.aspx?StateFIPS=46&StateName=South%20Dakota#.U8LWu_ldUeo South Dakota State Facts from USDA]\n* [http://www.sdshspress.com/ South Dakota State Historical Society Press]\n* {{Cite Collier's | wstitle = South Dakota}}\n* {{curlie|Regional/North_America/United_States/South_Dakota}}\n* {{osmrelation-inline|161652}}\n* [http://dakotapathways.org/ Dakota Pathways]\n* [http://historicalregistry.com/?page_id=241 Joe J. Foss, Medal of Honor]\n{{clear}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[North Dakota]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of U.S. states by date of statehood]]|years=Admitted on November 2, 1889 (40th)}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Montana]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title = <span style=\"font-size:11pt;\">Topics related to South Dakota</span><br />''The Mount Rushmore State ''\n|list =\n{{South Dakota|expanded}}\n{{Protected areas of South Dakota}}\n{{Midwestern United States}}\n{{New France}}\n{{New Spain}}\n{{United States political divisions}}\n|state=expanded}}\n\n{{Good article}}\n{{Coord|display=title|44.5|N|100|W|region:US-SD_type:adm1st_scale:3000000}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2013}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:South Dakota| ]]\n[[Category:States of the United States]]\n[[Category:States and territories established in 1889]]\n[[Category:Midwestern United States]]\n[[Category:U.S. states with multiple time zones]]\n[[Category:1889 establishments in the United States]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the U.S. state of South Dakota}}\n{{pp-pc1}}\n{{pp-move-indef}}\n{{Infobox U.S. state\n|name                    = South Dakota\n|official_name           = State of South Dakota\n|image_flag              = Flag of South Dakota.svg\n|flag_link               = Flag of South Dakota\n|image_seal              = SouthDakota-StateSeal.svg\n|image_map               = South Dakota in United States.svg\n|nickname                = The Mount Rushmore State (official)\n|motto                   = Under God the People Rule\n|anthem           