n\n| title2          = Mahiya Duur Gaya\n| extra2          = Umair Ahmed \n| length2         = 5:40\n\n| title3          = Tu Mila Hai\n| extra3         =Saad Sultan\n| length3        = 1:22\n\n| title4          = Aj Se\n| extra4          = Rizwan Anwar \n| length4         = 1:15\n}}\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Critical appreciation===\nSadaf Siddiqui of [[Dawn News]] states that ''Mera Naam Yousuf Hai is off to a smooth start''<ref name=MNYH>{{cite web|title=Mera Naam Yousuf Hai is off to a smooth start|accessdate= 15 October 2015|newspaper=[[Dawn (newspaper)|Dawn]]|author=Sadaf Siddiqui|date= 7 March 2015|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1167989}}</ref> in her issue she praised Writer's story line stating ''Writer Khalil-ur-Rehman Qamar\u2019s pen aspires to the tragic, the epic, and the unusual, and as his previous drama Pyare Afzal has shown, in some cases it succeeds'' she also praised [[Mehreen Jabbar]] as director stating ''Director Mehreen Jabbar managed to keep Khalil sahib\u2019s flair for drama under her subtle control. She hasn't let the dialogue overpower the narrative. It helps that the drama's production values are excellent as is the visual story telling with hints at the character's inner lives''.<ref name=\"MNYH\"/> She lauded [[Maya Ali (actress)|Maya Alli]], [[Imran Abbas Naqvi]] and [[Hina Khawaja Bayat]]'s role by saying ''Maya Ali\u2019s restrained performance as Zulekha proves she's a director\u2019s actor and so far Mehreen Jabbar has guided her well. Imran Abbas, who seems perennially youthful, also, pardon the pun, strikes a chord as the dreamer Yousuf. But if there was an actor who stole the spotlight today, it has to be Hina Khwaja Bayat.''<ref name=\"MNYH\"/>\n\nSiddiqui, on her other issue  praised the shows plot and melodrama stating \"TV drama Mera Naam Yousuf Hai plays the filmi card and wins\". She further added that \"It isn't merely filmi in the sense that it features over-the-top melodrama; there are also a fair number of larger-than-life events to contend with. These events aren't just plot points pushing the story forward, they're like cogs in a vast machine that represent the characters' interconnected, messy lives.\"<ref name=\"MNYH plays film card\">{{cite web|title=TV drama Mera Naam Yousuf Hai plays the filmi card and wins|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1189372|author= Sadaf Siddiqui|date= 22 June 2015|publisher=Dawn}}</ref> She commented on [[Khalil-Ur-Rehman Qamar]]'s screenplay stating that \"Khalil sahib's script brings into question society\u2019s hypocrisies and double standards, as well as the different roles, expectations and allowances for men and women.\" She also praised Mehreen Jabbar's directory saying \"It is quite commendable that despite all these filmi touches and a tendency to go over the top, Mehreen Jabbar's directorial hand is very much in control.\"<ref name=\"MNYH plays film card\"/> In an issue of ''[[Dawn (newspaper)|Dawn]]'' 6 April 2015, Sadaf Siddiqui  stated that \"Mera Naam Yousuf Hai is a One sided Love story so far\" she comments not the plot stating \"What does one do when one\u2019s own parents are engaged in a game of one-upmanship, placing one\u2019s freedom and right to choose in jeopardy?\".<ref name=\"MNYH on sided love story\">{{cite web|title=Mera Naam Yousuf Hai is a one sided love story so far|author=Sadaf Siddiqui|publisher=Dawn|accessdate=15 October 2015|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1174283|date=6 April 2015}}</ref> For the current episode arc Sadaf once again praised Qamar's classic storyline stating \"Khalilur Rehman Qamar\u2019s writing sparkles with wit and clearly unke kamaan pe bahut se teer hai. The way the story and each of the characters is revealed adds something new to the plot progression and builds on each characters back stories.\"<ref name=\"MNYH on sided love story\"/>\n\nOn 29 July 2015, Sadaf Siddui's praised the show's screenplay and storyline commenting \"Do class concerns trump love? Mera Naam Yousuf Hai asks big questions\". In her article she said that \"Writer creates chemistry and romantic tension between the leads despite them not sharing much screen time. It is sheer mastery that makes allowance for conservatism and added that he carefully tends to family relationships and friendships.\"<ref name=\"MNYH asks big questions\">{{cite web|title=Do class concerns trump love? Mera Naam Yousuf Hai asks big questions|accessdate=15 October 2015|date=29 July 2015|publisher=Dawn|author=Sadaf Siddiqui|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1196299}}</ref> After summing up the entire show and story line, Siddiqui said that \"The drama makes important observations about power: in our patriarchal society and its lopsided and unfair ways, people use power to perpetuate their own interests and maintain the status quo.\" She also praised the series conclusion where she added that \"The biggest surprise perhaps was that Khalil sahib allowed the lovers to reunite, however not without a near death experience\",<ref name=\"MNYH asks big questions\"/> the series was one of Qamar's screen play where the protagonist were united and not deceased, this point attracted several viewers to it. It is the only drama to air on the famous Indian channel [[Star Plus]].\n\n==See also==\n* ''[[Tum Kon Piya]]''\n* ''[[Sadqay Tumhare]]''\n* [[Yusuf and Zulaikha]]\n* [[Zuleika (given name)|Zulekha]]\n* [[Yusuf]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|3}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://a-plus.tv/programs_details.php?d=8 official website]\n* {{IMDb title|tt4771342}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:A-Plus Entertainment television series]]\n[[Category:2015 Pakistani television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2014 Pakistani television series endings]]\n[[Category:Pakistani drama television series]]\n[[Category:Urdu-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Urdu language telenovelas]]\n[[Category:Pakistani telenovelas]]\n[[Category:Mehreen Jabbar's directions]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Pakistani English|date=March 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Mera Naam Yousuf Hai\n| image                = Mera Naam Yusuf Hai official poster.jpg\n| caption              = Title screen of ''Mera Naam Yousuf Hai'' \n| show_name_2          = ''Zulaikha Bina Yousuf''\n| genre                = [[Romance film|Romantic]] [[drama]]\n| writer               = [[Khalil-Ur-Rehman Qamar]]\n| based_on             = \n| director             = [[Mehreen Jabbar]]\n| starring             = [[Imran Abbas Naqvi|Imran Abbas]]<br / > [[Maya Ali (actress)|Maya Ali]]<br /> [[Mansha Pasha]]<br /> [[Waseem Abbas]]<br />[[Hina Khawaja Bayat]]<br />[[Faizan Shaikh]]\n| theme_music_composer = Sultan Athor\n| opentheme            = \"Tu Mera Nahi\"<br />by Saad Sultan & Imran Abbas\n| composer             = Saad Sultan\n| country              = [[Pakistan]]\n| language             = [[Urdu language|Urdu]]\n| num_episodes         = 20\n| list_episodes         = #Episodes\n| producer             = [[Sadia Jabbar]] \n| executive_producer   = Abid Ul Razaq\n| editor               = Farooq Javed<br />Majid Riaz \n| location             = [[Karachi]], [[Sindh]], [[Pakistan]]\n| cinematography       = Qasim Ali Mureed\n| camera               = [[Multi-Camera]]\n| runtime              = 35-40 minutes \n| company              = [[Sadia Jabbar Production]]\n| channel              = [[A-Plus Entertainment]]\n| picture_format       = 560ii ([[SDTV]])<br/>720pp ([[HDTV]])\n| first_run            = Pakistan\n| first_aired          = {{Start date|df=yes|2015|03|06}} \n| last_aired           = {{Start date|df=yes|2015|07|17}} \n| website                  = http://www.a-plus.tv/\n| website_title            = A-Plus Entertainment \n| production_website       = \n| production_website_title = \n}}\n<!-- As per [[WP:MOSBEGIN]] the lead paragraph shall be illustrated in the way provided below, this paragraph has been compared by [[WP:MOSBEGIN]] illustrated point, removal of item such as premier dates, timings, stories, leading crew members, etc. will be wrong, these details are required by wikipedia and are provided, they should not be removed. Before any edits to this please go through [[WP:MOSBEGIN]], removal of these will cause conflicts.-->\n'''''Mera Naam Yousuf Hai''''' ({{lang-ur|{{Nastaliq|\u0645\u06cc\u0631\u0627 \u0646\u0627\u0645 \u06cc\u0648\u0633\u0641 \u06c1\u06d2}}}}, \"My name is Yousuf\"), previously titled as '''''Zulekha Bina Yusuf'''''<ref>{{cite web|title=Zulekha Bina Yousuf|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1147642|publisher=Dawn News|accessdate=7 March 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"brandsynaro\">{{cite web|title=Zulekha Bina Yusuf Coming Soon on Aplus: OST & Timings|url=http://www.brandsynario.com/zulekha-bina-yusuf-coming-soon-on-aplus-ost-timings|accessdate=11 June 2015|publisher=brandsynaro}}</ref> ({{nq|\u0632\u0644\u06cc\u062e\u0627 \u0628\u0646\u0627 \u06cc\u0648\u0633\u0641}}, \"Yousuf without Zulekha\"), is a Pakistani television [[Pakistani drama|drama serial]], which originally aired on the [[A-Plus Entertainment]] from 17 March 2015, to 27 October 2015, comprising a total of 20 episodes. ''Mera Naam Yousuf Hai'' follows a Forbidden Love Story of Yousuf and Zulaikha. The story is told in a heavily serialised manner. It faces a love triangle between characters Yousuf, Zulaikha and Madiha, features a mother's love for her daughters, a father's hatred, a lover's sacrifices, and the pain for love.\n\n''Mera Naam Yousuf Hai'' stars [[Maya Ali (actress)|Maya Ali]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Review: Mera Naam Yousuf Hai is a one-sided love story so far|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1174283|date=6 April 2015|accessdate=14 June 2015|author=Sadaf Siddique|publisher=Dawn.com}}</ref> and [[Imran Abbas Naqvi]]<ref name=\"Press release\"/> as the title characters [[Zulaikha]] and [[Yusuf]], respectively. And star [[Hina Khawaja Bayat]], [[Waseem Abbas]], [[Behroze Sabzwari]], [[Mizna Waqas]] and [[Mansha Pasha]] in recurring roles. Series was produced by Saadia Jabbar, and aired on A-plus entertainment as part of a night programming of 20:00. It was written by [[Khalil-Ur-Rehman Qamar]]<ref name=\"Press release\">{{cite web|title=Imran Abbas plays title character in Mera Naam Yousuf Hai|date=4 March 2015|accessdate=11 June 2015|publisher=Daily Times|url=http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/entertainment/04-Mar-2015/imran-abbas-plays-title-character-in-mera-naam-yousuf-hai|author=Press release}}</ref><ref name=\"Falak\">{{cite web|title=Mera Naam Yousuf Hai|accessdate=11 June 2015|publisher=Drama Pakistani|author=Falak|url=http://www.dramapakistani.net/mera-naam-yousuf-hai/}}</ref> and directed by [[Mehreen Jabbar]]<ref name=\"reviewit.pk\">{{cite web|title=Zulekha Bina Yusuf, Mehreen Jabbar confirms the new project|author=Rashid Nazir Ali|publisher=review it|date=27 November 2014|accessdate=11 June 2015|url=http://reviewit.pk/zulekha-bina-yusuf-mehreen-jabbar-confirms-the-new-project/}}</ref>. ''Mera Naam Yousuf Hai'' premiered in Pakistan on 6 March 2015, with prime slot on Fridays<ref name=\"autogenerated2\">{{cite web|title=A-Plus Drama serial: ''MERA NAAM YOUSUF HAI''|url=http://www.breakingnewspak.com/a-plus-drama-serial-mera-naam-yousuf-hai/|publisher=Breaking News|accessdate=13 March 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[Star India]] begin its airing on 19 October 2015 on their channel [[Star Plus]]-thus becoming the channel's first ever Pakistani drama. The series was aired in India, UAE, USA, Ireland, UK, Austria, Europe, Canada and Latin America. Series received extravagant reception in viewership and ratings.<ref>{{cite web|title=''Mera Naam Yusuf Hai'' to hit the screens on Indian Channel|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1147642|publisher=Dawn News|accessdate=7 March 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Rashid Nazir Ali\">{{cite web|title=''Mera Naam Yusuf Hai'' to be aired on Star Plus|author=Rashid Nazir Ali|publisher=review it|date=27 November 2014|accessdate=11 June 2015|url=http://reviewit.pk/zulekha-bina-yusuf-mehreen-jabbar-confirms-the-new-project/}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n\nThe story revolves around the forbidden love of Yousuf and Zulaikha. Yousuf first saw Zulaikha in a trainand is unable to get her out of his mind. Zulaikha on the other hand, considered it a momentary attraction as she is stuck between her cousin's marriage proposals, masked by the personal interests of her parents. She bumps into Yousuf several times who is evidently in love with her and is expressive about his feelings for her. Later, Noor Muhammad, Zulaikha's Father announces her marriage with Imran Moeez (his nephew) so he himself can marry Imran's Aunt Bushra. Yousuf tries to prove his love to Zulaikha so she can deny marrying Imran. The story takes turn when the police torture Yousuf upon Noor Muhammad's orders, at this point Zulaikha becomes aware that his love for her has always been true. Looking to this Zulaikha eventually falls in love with Yousuf. Afiya Begum, Zulaikha's mother and Hajira, Zulaikha's sister then start to support her to marry Yousuf while Noor Muhammad starts threatening them, he however marries with Bushra successfully. Story shows women power against Noor and shows how the three women team up. Later, a hidden past is revealed to Yousuf and Zulaikha conveying that both are not made for each other and separation is in their destiny, despite this both show reluctance and tend to name their love, the two faced equal tortures. The Story is penned on the challenges, tortures and sacrifices they face for their love, and shows how Afiya protects her daughter's from their father, and survives all his tortures.<ref name=\"Falak\"/><ref>{{cite web|title= Mera Naam Yusuf Hai|url=http://a-plus.tv/programs_details.php?d=8}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Mera Naam Yousuf Hai is off to a smooth start|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1167989|publisher=Dawn|date=7 March 2015|accessdate=11 June 2015|author=Sadaf Siddique}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title= Mera Naam Yousuf hai is a one-sided love story so far|accessdate=22 September 2015|author=Sadaf Siddique|publisher=Dawn|date= 6 April 2015|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1174283}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\n\n''Mera Naam Yousaf Hai'' was developed by producer Sadia Jabbar of Sadia Jabbar Productions, she hired successful director [[Mehreen Jabbar]] to direct the series. The Show is written by famous writer [[Khalil-ur-Rehman Qamar]],<ref name=\"Press release\"/> the show is loosely based on the story of ''[[Yusuf and Zulaikha]]'' by [[Jami]] in his book ''[[Haft Awrang]]'' with some edits, the screenplay is also written by Khalil-ur-Rehman Qamar while Script composing is done by Naman Ali. Approximately with twenty-one episodes, [[Yusuf and Zulaikha|Zulaikha Bina Yousuf]] was completed in February 2015 and was all set to premier on 12 March 2015 with a prime slot of Thursday 8:00pm.<ref>{{cite web|title=Zulekha Bina Yusuf Coming Soon on Aplus OST & Timings|url=http://www.brandsynario.com/zulekha-bina-yusuf-coming-soon-on-aplus-ost-timings|accessdate=11 June 2015|publisher=brandsynaro}}</ref> However, in mid-March 2015 promotional team gave the show a new title ''Mera Naam Yousuf Hai'' and changed its premier to 6 March 2015. Song composition is done by Sultan Athor while the [[Open Source Track|OST]] given by Saad Sultan. The show aired weekly episode for 35 - 40 (without commercials) minutes every Friday to 18 July 2015.\n\nProducer [[Sadia Jabbar]] choose, [[Imran Abbas Naqvi]] and [[Maya Ali (actress)|Maya Ali]] to play the leading roles of Yousof and Zulaikha, respectively. Imran Abbas<ref>{{cite web|title=Fashion Feature: A Guy Thing|url=http://archives.dawn.com/weekly/images/archive/080824/images7.htm|publisher=Dawn|accessdate=15 August 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Interview of Imran Abbas|url=http://www.fashioncentral.pk/people-parties/celebrity-interviews/story-73-imran-abbas-interview|publisher=Fashion Central|accessdate=15 August 2013}}</ref> joined the shoot. [[Maya Ali (actress)|Maya Ali]] was selected to role for the character of Zulaikha. The actors [[Mansha Pasha]], Waseem Abbas, [[Behroze Sabzwari]], [[Hina Khawaja Bayat]] and Seema Seher were selected to portray Madiha, Noor Muhammad, Waji Ahmed, Afiya and Hajira, respectively.\n\nThe filming of drama serial begin in September/October 2014 and was completed in late January 2015.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\"/> under the title ''Zulaikha Bina Yousuf''.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\">{{cite web|title=Mehreen Jabbar all set for Zulekha Bina Yusuf|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1147642}}</ref> Zulaikha Bina Yousuf's premiere was announced on 12 March 2015 with Thursday 8:00pm as a prime slot.<ref name=\"brandsynaro\"/> On 2 March 2015 it was announced that the title is changed to Mera Naam Yousauf hai with Friday 8:00pm as a prime slot, the premier was then decided to be launched during 6 March 2015.<ref name=\"autogenerated2\"/>\n\n==Cast ==\n{{Multiple image\n | direction = horizontal\n | total_width = 240\n | image1    = Imran Abbas at 'Jaanisaar' screening.jpg\n | caption1    =[[Imran Abbas]] \n | image2    = \n | caption2    =[[Maya Ali]] \n}}\n\n* [[Imran Abbas (actor)|Imran Abbas]] as Yousuf Waji Ahmed \n* [[Maya Ali (actress)|Maya Ali]] as Zulaikha Noor Mohammed\n* [[Waseem Abbas]] as Molvi Noor Mohammed/ Sheikh Sahab \n* [[Mansha Pasha]] as Madiha \n* Anas Ali Imran as Tony\n* [[Hina Khawaja Bayat]] as Aafiya Begum \n* Perveen Akbar as Kausar Parveen \n* [[Mizna Waqas]] as Hajira Noor Mohammed \n* [[Behroze Sabzwari]] as Waji Ahmed \n* Seema Seher as Yousuf's mother \n* Ali Sheikh as Tajee \n* Taqi Ahmed as Imran Moeez\n* [[Faizan Shaikh]] as Wali \n* Farah Nadeem as Bushra\n\n==Episodes==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width:99%;\"\n|-\n! Episode  !! Episode Summary !! Run time !! Release Date !! Viewers    \n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#CC9900;\"|\n|-\n|  1 || Story starts by showing Yousuf who just travelled to Karachi and has come to his friend's house; he tells him about his travelling. He tells him that he had accidentally entered a train after missing his actually one, luckily this train was taking him to the same place. He sees Zulaikha and is unable to keep his eyes away from her, he finds out that she is the daughter of a Maulvi and her father is very strict on his daughters, he tells Yousuf to jump out of the train on the next station. When the train approaches the next station, Zulaikha along with her sister Hajira gets out of it for a walk and Yousuf after looking that she is away from her dad, asks her if her name was Zulaikha she denies and leaves. It is told that Yousuf is a singer and believes that one day he would change his destiny. Zulaikha on the other hand is shown to be belonged to a very strict father but polite mother who always stands for her children especially daughters. Noor Muhammad (Zulaikha's father) comes to Afiya Begum (Zulaikha's mother) and tells her that his sister, Kausar Parveen (Zulaikha's aunt) wants Zulaikha to marry her son (Imran Mughees).<ref>{{cite web|title= Review of episode 1 of MNYH|url=http://desirantsnraves.com/2015/03/06/mera-naam-yousuf-hai-episode-1-review/}}</ref> || 39:05 || 6 March 2015 || 68,100<ref>{{cite web|title=Star Plus rules Sunday with new shows|author=Raj Badhaan|publisher=Media 24/7|accessdate= 30 November 2015|date=19 October 2015|url=http://www.media247.co.uk/bizasia/overnights-star-plus-uk-rules-sunday-with-new-shows-2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#CC9900;\"|\n|-\n| 2 || Imran Mughees is Zulaikha's cousin whom she fully dislikes because of his character. Zulaikha's mother tells her that if she wants to reject Imran Mughees, she must marry her other cousin Ali Hamza who is Afia's nephew. Now Zulaikha is stuck between these two proposals and wants to get out of them. Yousuf comes to Zulaikha's door. He says that he is a postman and has a parcel for Zulaikha, when she comes to the door she recognises him just when Yousuf tell her his name. He then leaves on his bike.<ref>{{cite web|title=review of episode 2 of MNYH|url= http://desirantsnraves.com/2015/03/06/mera-naam-yousuf-hai-episode-1-review/}}</ref> || 37:45 || 13 March 2015 || 38,100<ref>{{cite web|title=Big Boss climbs up on Sunday|author=Raj Badhaan|publisher=Media 24/7|accessdate= 30 November 2015|date=26 October 2015|url=http://www.media247.co.uk/bizasia/overnights-bigg-boss-9-climbs-up-on-sunday-2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#CC9900;\"|\n|-\n|  3 || Afiya invites her sister (Ali Hamza's mother) to live with them for ten days, the real purpose is to bring the marriage proposal which Noor Muhammad denies verbally. On the other hand, its told that Yousuf's friend Taji's sister Madiha has hidden feelings for him and calls him on phone which Yousuf dislikes, she tells him that she is his friend and he can share any thing with her, verbally aware of the truth Yousuf tells her that he loves Zulaikha and she must take convince her, deeply hurt Madiha agrees. Zulaikha and Yusouf dream about each other. Yousuf's mother listens to him talking to his friend and is now aware of his love interest. She tells his father who asks him about Zulaikha, Yousuf ignores the conversation and flies it as a joke. Zulaikha's father asks her about her choice of wedding, he yells and questions her just then Zulaikha denies both the proposals and says that she would marry whom she wants and according to her religion she is given full permission.<ref>{{cite web|title= Review of Episode 3 of MNYUH|url=http://reviewit.pk/mera-naam-yousuf-hai-episode-3/}}</ref> || 35:25 || 20 March 2015 || 64,200<ref>{{cite web|title=Star Plus' Sunday ratings increase|author=Raj Badhaan|publisher=Media 24/7|accessdate= 30 November 2015|date=2 November 2015|url=http://www.media247.co.uk/bizasia/overnights-star-plus-sunday-uk-ratings-increase-further-2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#CC9900;\"|\n|-\n| 4 || Yousuf asks Madiha to talk to Zulaikha for him, Madiha realises that if she has true feelings than she must 