n her face is uncovered she shocks Noor and Imraan's family. || 38:00 || 5 June 2015  \n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#CC9900;\"|\n|-\n| 15 || Hajira is bought back to Afiya by Noor Muhammad, he swears that he will bring Zulaikha back. The Next day Yousuf, on his bike takes Zulaikha to a layer and after visiting the court Zulaikha's divorce case from Imran Moeez in filed. Noor Muhammad goes to Yousuf's home and finds out that Yosusf is Waji Ahmed's Son, and leaves. On their way back Yousuf and Zulaikha are stuck between Noor Muhammad's goons led by Wali and Imran. Yousuf fights for Zulaikha ending up himself being beaten, Zulaikha then strokes a rock on Imran's head who gained every ones attention. After this she helps Yousuf to stand through her support and rushes, the two escape with goons chasing them, after few goons caught them Yousuf hits them and the two are finally successful. Yousuf is now sully sure that Zulaikha loves him. Later Madiha visits Yousuf and Zulaikha and upon Waji Ahmed's insisting she stays there with Zulaikha and Mahrukh for a day. || 38:00 || 12 June 2015  \n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#CC9900;\"|\n|-\n| 16 || Madiha and Tajee insist Zulaikha to live with them for protection, when Waji Ahmed and Yousuf to ask her she agrees. Madiha introduces Zulaikha to her house and both try to bond, Zulaikha is suspicious on her that she once loved Yousuf. Later, Noor Muhammad, and Wali bring their goons at Tajee's home and forcefully beat them, Zulaikha then asks Noor to stop selling her which leads him to raise his hand, Zulaikha faints and is taken back, Madiha informs Hajira about this. || 37:50 || 19 June 2015 \n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#CC9900;\"|\n|-\n| 17 || Zulekha is tied chain and is tortured, while Yousuf is tortured by the police, it is shown that both of them faced torture and are helpless, Zulaikha swears in front of Kausar Paveen that she will both let this go easily. Noor Muhammad finally Bushra and promises to gift him a three lac rupee cheque. Afiya slaps Wali and tells him to get out of her house. Wali feels guilty for his doings. Madiha took care of yousuf in hospital, looking to her Yousuf's mother asks her to confront her love in front of them, Madiha says that she does not love Yousuf as she knows that he is only for Zulaikha. It is revealed that it was Tajee who helped Noor Muhammad to find Zulaikha's location. Kausar gets irked looking at Imraan supporting Zulaikha. || 37:00 || 26 June 2015 \n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#CC9900;\"|\n|-\n| 18 || Imraan starts supporting Zulaikha and objects Kausar to end her fight which brooke out only for a momentary comment of Afiya. Kausar Parveen gets Irked. Imraan leaves Zulaikha to her home and goes back. Zulaikha is now separated from him. Wali took away Noor Muhammad's entire money, property, and left overs and moved to Dubai, Afiya finds out few documents proving Noor Muhammad wrong. Noor Muhammad is shocked to hear about his money being taken and gets worried. Zulaikha tells Hajra that nothing happened in her wedding night and flashbacks prove that Zulaikha accused Kausar for destroying her family, and  Imraan felt guilty, which made him to support her. || 38:00 || 3 July 2015 \n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#CC9900;\"|\n|-\n| 19 || Zulaikha narrates her first wedding experience with Imraan to Hajira. Yousuf Proposes to Madiha, Madiha declines. Imraan leaves to Dubai divorcing Zulaikha. Noor asks Afiya about Wali and she replies that he has left his father. She takes her daughters and leaves, and start living in a new apartment. Yousuf takes Madiha on a dinner. Noor Muhammad lost all his fate and became poor. || 39:00 || 10 July 2015 \n|- \n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#CC9900;\"|\n|-\n| 20 || Zulaikha starts a job, she finds out that she is working on Waji Ahmed's office who comes to know of his divorce. Yousuf insists Madiha to marry him, Madiha says that she will only agree if Zulaikha will sit next to her. Waji Ahmed visits Zulaikha, he narrates his entire past with Afiya to Zulaikha telling her that he is spending his life in depression. Afiya, Hajra and Waji insist Zulaikha to marry Yousuf but Zulaikha declines. Yousuf starts a high-paying job and finally accepts his step-mother and tends to move on. Madiha and Yousuf's marriage function starts, Zulaikha and Hajra attends. By the time of Nikkah, when Yousuf is asked to declare his acceptance, he repeats two times, when he is about to announce it the third time, Zulaikha faints, Yousuf gets worried, when she gains conscious she found herself in the hospital. She is shocked when asked for Nikkah declaration, Madiha and Afiya insist and she finally accepts. Yousuf and Zulaikha are now married and Madiha happily moves on. || 40:44 || 17 July 2015 \n|-\n|}\n\n==Soundtrack==\nThe theme songs were Saad Sultan and were performed by singers like Rizwan Anwar, Saad Sultan, Imran Abbas himself and Umair Ahmed. It was written by the composing team itself. The lines of the song are frequently used during the course of the show. The music video was released In March 2015.\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Mera Naam Yousuf hai\n| type         = soundtrack\n| artist       = Saad Sultan and Rizwan Anwar\n| cover        = \n| released     = February 2015\n| recorded     = 2014\n| genre        = [[Theme song]]\n| length       = {{Duration|m=2|s=21}}<br />{{Duration|m=1|s=10}}\n| language     = [[Urdu language|Urdu]]\n| label        = \n| producer     = Sadia Jabbar\n| misc         = [http://www.dramaindustry.tv/video_Mera-Naam-Yousuf-Hai-OST-Title-Song---Official_3749 Music Video]\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline        = Track list\n| extra_column    = Singer(s)\n| total_length    = \n| title1          = Tu Mera Nahi\n| extra1          = Rizwan Anwar<br />Imran Abbas<br>Saad Sultan\n| length1         = 2:21\n\n| title2          = Mahiya Duur Gaya\n| extra2          = Umair Ahmed \n| length2         = 5:40\n\n| title3          = Tu Mila Hai\n| extra3         =Saad Sultan\n| length3        = 1:22\n\n| title4          = Aj Se\n| extra4          = Rizwan Anwar \n| length4         = 1:15\n}}\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Critical appreciation===\nSadaf Siddiqui of [[Dawn News]] states that ''Mera Naam Yousuf Hai is off to a smooth start''<ref name=MNYH>{{cite web|title=Mera Naam Yousuf Hai is off to a smooth start|accessdate= 15 October 2015|newspaper=[[Dawn (newspaper)|Dawn]]|author=Sadaf Siddiqui|date= 7 March 2015|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1167989}}</ref> in her issue she praised Writer's story line stating ''Writer Khalil-ur-Rehman Qamar\u2019s pen aspires to the tragic, the epic, and the unusual, and as his previous drama Pyare Afzal has shown, in some cases it succeeds'' she also praised [[Mehreen Jabbar]] as director stating ''Director Mehreen Jabbar managed to keep Khalil sahib\u2019s flair for drama under her subtle control. She hasn't let the dialogue overpower the narrative. It helps that the drama's production values are excellent as is the visual story telling with hints at the character's inner lives''.<ref name=\"MNYH\"/> She lauded [[Maya Ali (actress)|Maya Alli]], [[Imran Abbas Naqvi]] and [[Hina Khawaja Bayat]]'s role by saying ''Maya Ali\u2019s restrained performance as Zulekha proves she's a director\u2019s actor and so far Mehreen Jabbar has guided her well. Imran Abbas, who seems perennially youthful, also, pardon the pun, strikes a chord as the dreamer Yousuf. But if there was an actor who stole the spotlight today, it has to be Hina Khwaja Bayat.''<ref name=\"MNYH\"/>\n\nSiddiqui, on her other issue  praised the shows plot and melodrama stating \"TV drama Mera Naam Yousuf Hai plays the filmi card and wins\". She further added that \"It isn't merely filmi in the sense that it features over-the-top melodrama; there are also a fair number of larger-than-life events to contend with. These events aren't just plot points pushing the story forward, they're like cogs in a vast machine that represent the characters' interconnected, messy lives.\"<ref name=\"MNYH plays film card\">{{cite web|title=TV drama Mera Naam Yousuf Hai plays the filmi card and wins|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1189372|author= Sadaf Siddiqui|date= 22 June 2015|publisher=Dawn}}</ref> She commented on [[Khalil-Ur-Rehman Qamar]]'s screenplay stating that \"Khalil sahib's script brings into question society\u2019s hypocrisies and double standards, as well as the different roles, expectations and allowances for men and women.\" She also praised Mehreen Jabbar's directory saying \"It is quite commendable that despite all these filmi touches and a tendency to go over the top, Mehreen Jabbar's directorial hand is very much in control.\"<ref name=\"MNYH plays film card\"/> In an issue of ''[[Dawn (newspaper)|Dawn]]'' 6 April 2015, Sadaf Siddiqui  stated that \"Mera Naam Yousuf Hai is a One sided Love story so far\" she comments not the plot stating \"What does one do when one\u2019s own parents are engaged in a game of one-upmanship, placing one\u2019s freedom and right to choose in jeopardy?\".<ref name=\"MNYH on sided love story\">{{cite web|title=Mera Naam Yousuf Hai is a one sided love story so far|author=Sadaf Siddiqui|publisher=Dawn|accessdate=15 October 2015|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1174283|date=6 April 2015}}</ref> For the current episode arc Sadaf once again praised Qamar's classic storyline stating \"Khalilur Rehman Qamar\u2019s writing sparkles with wit and clearly unke kamaan pe bahut se teer hai. The way the story and each of the characters is revealed adds something new to the plot progression and builds on each characters back stories.\"<ref name=\"MNYH on sided love story\"/>\n\nOn 29 July 2015, Sadaf Siddui's praised the show's screenplay and storyline commenting \"Do class concerns trump love? Mera Naam Yousuf Hai asks big questions\". In her article she said that \"Writer creates chemistry and romantic tension between the leads despite them not sharing much screen time. It is sheer mastery that makes allowance for conservatism and added that he carefully tends to family relationships and friendships.\"<ref name=\"MNYH asks big questions\">{{cite web|title=Do class concerns trump love? Mera Naam Yousuf Hai asks big questions|accessdate=15 October 2015|date=29 July 2015|publisher=Dawn|author=Sadaf Siddiqui|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1196299}}</ref> After summing up the entire show and story line, Siddiqui said that \"The drama makes important observations about power: in our patriarchal society and its lopsided and unfair ways, people use power to perpetuate their own interests and maintain the status quo.\" She also praised the series conclusion where she added that \"The biggest surprise perhaps was that Khalil sahib allowed the lovers to reunite, however not without a near death experience\",<ref name=\"MNYH asks big questions\"/> the series was one of Qamar's screen play where the protagonist were united and not deceased, this point attracted several viewers to it. It is the only drama to air on the famous Indian channel [[Star Plus]].\n\n==See also==\n* ''[[Tum Kon Piya]]''\n* ''[[Sadqay Tumhare]]''\n* [[Yusuf and Zulaikha]]\n* [[Zuleika (given name)|Zulekha]]\n* [[Yusuf]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|3}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://a-plus.tv/programs_details.php?d=8 official website]\n* {{IMDb title|tt4771342}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:A-Plus Entertainment television series]]\n[[Category:2015 Pakistani television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2014 Pakistani television series endings]]\n[[Category:Pakistani drama television series]]\n[[Category:Urdu-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Urdu language telenovelas]]\n[[Category:Pakistani telenovelas]]\n[[Category:Mehreen Jabbar's directions]]\n", "name_user": "Jellysandwich0", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mera_Naam_Yousuf_Hai"}
